his.  This item is created by casting the spell &quot;Dance of the Fireflies&quot;.  It can only be cast at night so be certain to have one already made when VSR is pulled since if he is pulled in the daytime you will not be able to do the quest.  Actually not a bad idea to have two people with a globe just in case the main quester has the bad manners to go LD just as VSR is pulled.  After VSR goes through his lines, hand him the &quot;Firefly Globe&quot;.  VSR will despawn and Venril Sathir's Spirit (VSS) will spawn.  He will also run through his script, the keyword of which is &quot;resurrection&quot; I believe.  You will need to have a spell scroll of the level 49 (has to be the level 49 one) cleric spell Resurrection (bought mine at the cleric's guild in NFP).  Upon receiving the scroll VSS will despawn and the fake Venril Sathir will spawn (called the &quot;fake&quot; because he is created by this quest, is weaker than the &quot;real&quot; VS, and only drops the quest stones as loot).  He will attack upon spawning, you kill him and gets the stones.<br>
<br>
     We took him out with 2 groups (levels 49-57) with only a couple of deaths.  Try to keep the questees alive through this so they can loot the stones upon the death of VS with minimal complications (unlike my own experience, heh).  The &quot;fake&quot; VS is level 51 and the &quot;real&quot; VS is level 55.  Both supposedly can cast a 1500pt lifetap.  Based on the posts I have read the &quot;fake&quot; one is not as likely to do so but can/does.  If the &quot;real&quot; VS is up it will require about twice as many people of the same levels to accomplish.  The &quot;real&quot; VS can drop the class-specific Kunark legs and some other items.  He does not drop the stones but upon his death, VSR will spawn and then you can do the quest for the stones but will be a tough fight doing the &quot;real&quot; and then the &quot;fake&quot; back-to-back that way.  I will try/probably attend as well but can't be certain until it gets closer to that time and I check the wife faction/agenda. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/blottdrinal>Lords of the Ters'Tai - Drinal</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/flottdrinalfrm2>Ters'Tai Barracks</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.terstai.net">Lords of the Ters'Tai</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.4.7<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  